---
// Terms of Sale & Refund Policy page — Cotton background, Noir text
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/navigation/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/navigation/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Sale & Refund Policy"
  description="Ncheta Magazine — Terms of Sale and Refund Policy."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <article class="prose-content">
      <header class="mb-10">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav
          class="mb-8 font-inter text-xs text-noir/40 flex gap-2"
          aria-label="Breadcrumb"
        >
          <a href="/" class="transition-colors">Home</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <span class="text-noir/60">Terms of Sale & Refund Policy</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="font-cinzel font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-noir mb-3">
          Terms of Sale and Refund Policy
        </h1>
      </header>

      <p class="mb-8 text-lg font-inter text-noir/80 leading-relaxed">
        By using our website or purchasing any of the services, you agree to be
        bound by these Terms of Sale and our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree
        with any part of these terms, you should stop using our website and
        refrain from making any purchases.
      </p>

      <ol class="space-y-6 list-none p-0">
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(i) Services:</strong> We offer various products and services,
            including but not limited to features and artist profiles, institutional
            and gallery coverage, documentation and archive support, advertising
            placements, newsletter advert placement, partnership and custom
            features.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(ii) Partnership and Custom Features:</strong> Each service
            may come with specific conditions, which will be described at the
            point of sale.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(iii) Purchase and Payment:</strong> When you make a purchase
            on Ncheta Magazine, you agree to provide current, complete, and
            accurate purchase and account information. All payments are
            processed using third-party payment solutions. By providing your
            payment information, you agree to their terms of use and acknowledge
            that you are responsible for any fees they may impose. The fees are
            always included in the retail price as indicated in your shopping
            cart.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(iv) Refund Policy:</strong> For our services, we do not
            provide refunds unless we agree that there is a valid reason for the
            request. Refunds, if any, will be granted at our sole discretion.
            Please note that transaction fees incurred from third-party payment
            solutions will not be refunded. All refund requests should be
            addressed by mail in writing to <a
              href="mailto:hello@nchetamagazine.com"
              class="text-cherry underline decoration-cherry/40 hover:decoration-cherry transition-colors"
              >hello@nchetamagazine.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(v) User Responsibilities:</strong> You agree to use our
            website and make purchases in accordance with all applicable laws and
            regulations and not for any unlawful purpose. You must not transmit
            any worms, viruses, or any code of a destructive nature.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(vi) Intellectual Property Rights:</strong> All content
            included on www.nchetamagazine.com, such as text, graphics, logos,
            images, services, downloads, as well as the compilation thereof, and
            any software used on the site, is the property of Ncheta Magazine or
            its suppliers and protected by copyright and other laws.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(vii) Limitation of Liability:</strong> Ncheta Magazine will
            not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, punitive, or
            consequential damages that result from the use of, or inability to
            use, our website or any services purchased through our website. When
            using our products in a legal or financial context, please note that
            it is the sole responsibility of the user to verify if the documents
            and instructions are legally enforceable according to local
            regulations, which may differ from region to region.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(viii) Changes to Terms of Sale:</strong> We reserve the right
            to update, change or replace any part of these Terms of Sale by
            posting updates and changes to our website. It is your responsibility
            to check our website periodically for changes.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>(ix) Contact Information:</strong> Questions about the Terms
            of Sale should be sent to us at <a
              href="mailto:hello@nchetamagazine.com"
              class="text-cherry underline decoration-cherry/40 hover:decoration-cherry transition-colors"
              >hello@nchetamagazine.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
